Section 1:
1 L.D. 1815
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 703, L.D. 1815, “An Act to Require a
10 Blood Test for Drugs for Drivers Involved in a Motor Vehicle Accident That Results in
11 Serious Bodily Injury or Death”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Require Testing for Intoxicants for Drivers Involved in a Motor Vehicle
14 Crash That Results in Serious Bodily Injury or Death'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 29-A MRSA §2401, sub-§5, as amended by PL 1995, c. 368, Pt. AAA, §4,
18 is further amended to read:
19 5. Failure to submit to a test, fails to submit to a test or failed to submit to a test.
20 "Failure to submit to a test," "fails to submit to a test" or "failed to submit to a test" means
21 failure to comply with the duty to submit to and complete a chemical test under section
22 2521, 2522-A or 2525.
23 Sec. 2. 29-A MRSA §2522-A is enacted to read:
24 §2522-A. Crashes; mandatory testing
25 1. Mandatory submission to test. If there is probable cause to believe that death or
26 serious bodily injury, as defined in Title 17-A, section 2, subsection 23, has occurred or
27 will occur as a result of a motor vehicle crash and that the operator of a motor vehicle
28 involved in the crash is under the influence of intoxicants, the operator shall submit to and
29 complete a chemical test or tests, including, but not limited to, a blood test, to determine
30 the presence or level of any drugs or alcohol in the operator's blood, breath or urine.
31 2. Suspension. The Secretary of State shall suspend, for a period of one year, the
32 license of a person who fails to submit to a chemical test or tests, including, but not limited
33 to, a blood test, under subsection 1. A suspension under this subsection must be in addition
34 to and consecutive with any other suspension under this Title or any other title, including
35 suspensions imposed pursuant to section 2451, 2453, 2521 or 2523.
Page 1 - 132LR1488(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 703, L.D. 1815
1 3. Scope of hearing. The scope of any hearing the Secretary of State holds pursuant
2 to section 2483 regarding a license suspension imposed under subsection 2 must include
3 whether there was probable cause to believe that the person who is the subject of the hearing
4 was the operator of a motor vehicle involved in a motor vehicle crash in which death or
5 serious bodily injury, as defined in Title 17-A, section 2, subsection 23, had occurred or
6 would occur, whether there was probable cause to believe that the person was under the
7 influence of intoxicants and whether the person failed to submit to and complete the
8 chemical test or tests under subsection 1.
9 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
10 allocations are made.
11 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
12 Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention 0143
13 Initiative: Provides one-time funding to equipment purchases.
14 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
15 Capital Expenditures $647,750 $0
16 __________ __________
17 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $647,750 $0
1184 Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention 0143
19 Initiative: Establishes 3 Chemist II positions to perform blood drug testing and blood
20 alcohol testing of motor vehicle operators if there is probable cause, assist with intake of
21 evidence, interpret test results, prepare analysis reports, review files and testify as an expert
22 witness in court. The initiative also provides funding for related All Other costs.
