2147 '
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2299 changes the title. The amendment requires an operator of a motor vehicle to submit to a
3300 chemical test or tests to determine the presence or level of any drugs or alcohol in the
3311 operator's blood, breath or urine if there is probable cause to believe that death or serious
3322 bodily injury has occurred or will occur as a result of a motor vehicle crash and the operator
3333 of a motor vehicle involved in the crash was under the influence of intoxicants. The
3344 amendment also requires the Secretary of State to suspend a person's license who fails to
3355 submit to that test with the suspension in addition to and consecutive with any other
3366 suspension.
3377 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3388 (See attached)
